name: L-lactate dehydrogenase (cytochrome)
names: cytochrome b2 (flavin-free derivative of flavocytochrome b2)
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
reaction: (S)-lactate + 2 ferricytochrome c = pyruvate + 2 ferrocytochrome c + 2 H+ [RN:R00196]
comment: Identical with cytochrome b2; a flavohemoprotein (FMN).
